title: For Sale:  BCM 14.5" Mid-Length AR-15 All Decked Out
postcontent:
I have a BCM (Bravo Company Mfg) AR-15 with Mid-length gas system and 14.5" barrel that I am selling.

The Rifle:

Both upper and lower receivers, barrel and bolt carrier group are all BCM.

The barrel is a 14.5" hammer forged chrome lined barrel. The BCG (Bolt Carrier Group) is is a full-auto size bolt and is HPT (High Pressure Tested) and MPI (Magnetic Particle Inspected) tested.

It has a Spikes Tactical buffer and Tubbs Flat Spring to help with recoil. 

It has a Magpul MIAD grip and CTR Stock. Magpul XTM rail covers ride on a Midwest Industries Free Floated Continuous rail. The vertical fore grip is a TangoDown.

It also has a KNS Precision Anti-Rotation Pins installed on it to keep the hammer and trigger pins from vibrating and backing out on you.

Optics & Light:

The primary optics is a Aimpoint Patrol Rifle Optic (brand new, only 1 month old) Red Dot Sight. It has night vision mode and will run for 3 years straight off of one battery on setting 7. Battery life is amazing on this thing!

For backup sights, the front sight is a standard A2 sight post with a tritium night sight inserted. The rear sight is a flip-up Troy BattleSight with tritium inserts. Great for using at night without the red dot. With the red dot on, the front post glows green on lower 1/3rd of aimpoint sight.

The weaponlight is a PentagonLight Xenon light with pressure switch. This light was used in Iraq on the battlefield, so it has a few scratches, but also tons of history. I think the switch needs some wiring work done.

Accessories it comes with:

It comes with an OD Green Voodoo Tactical Range Bag that carries 2 rifles.

It comes with 18 magazines, 5 are factory BCM metal magazines with Magpul non-tilt followers, 13 magazines are Magpul PMAG's with 4 being OD Green (I thought I wanted to switch over to OD Green furniture, so I bought 4 in OD Green.) and 9 being black.

---------------

This gun is fully mil-spec and is a total bad ass. It has never had a failure to feed, eject or fire. I have put 300 rounds through it (10 magazines full) and it ran flawlessly.

title: For Sale/Trade:  One of A Kind. Take a Look!!!
location: Michigan City area, South Bend, Indiana
postcontent: I have a 1943 57mm M70 Anti-Tank Round. The cool thing about it is someone put a sticker on it from 1955 Post Sugar Crisp cereal giveaway. For 2 box tops and .25c you could have your choice of team stickers. The sticker is made from cotton not paper and that's why it has lasted this long. The team is the 'Milwaukee Braves' and they were a team from 1953-1967 and the star of the team was Hank Aaron who started his career with them in 1954. The sticker promotion is thought to be the 1st ever team endorsement/cereal box offer ever. I challenge you to find 1 of these stickers for sale somewhere. They are very rare and the combination of the 2 items makes for a really cool conversation piece/ paper weight. It's a cross between World War 2 and Major League Baseball. The anti tank round is inert(not explosive) and is about 8" tall and 3" round and is commonly referred to as a '6 pounder'. I have no idea how to put a price on this thing so i am open to offers and if it sounds cool or interests me then we can make a deal.
